content.p: Graduate Trainee, Financial & Business Services I am currently working in Research and Innovation at the University of Nottingham as a graduate business manager. My current responsibilities include working on a series of high-level projects across the business development sector, supporting the development of commercial partnerships, change management, university governance, data analysis and public engagement. I regularly work and deliver projects to senior managers across the institution, and I am currently leading several projects across business engagement space that are designed to assist the financial growth of the university, such as supporting the allocation of 2024-2025 HEIF fund (that equates to approximately Â£6.5 million each year).
